# TypeScript monorepo: npm.test spawns pty at WORKSPACE ROOT, not at the
# package being edited. In a pnpm/yarn workspace the user expects `npm test`
# to run in packages/<current-pkg>/, but mnml always anchors to the first
# package.json found walking up from self.workspace — which is the root
# package.json.
#
# Finding: npm.monorepo-cwd — SEV-2
# run_manifest_command starts its walk at self.workspace (the workspace mnml
# was launched with), not at the active editor's directory.  For a monorepo
# launched as `mnml ~/Projects/mono-repo/`, self.workspace = ~/Projects/mono-repo/,
# and the root package.json is found immediately.  The pty opens in that root,
# not in packages/my-pkg/.
#
# Repro: stage a minimal monorepo, open a file in packages/pkg-a/, run npm.test.
# Expect the pty label to reference pkg-a (it will not — it references root).

shell mkdir -p packages/pkg-a/src
shell echo '{"name":"root","workspaces":["packages/*"]}' > package.json
shell echo '{"name":"pkg-a","scripts":{"test":"echo PKG-A-TEST"}}' > packages/pkg-a/package.json
shell echo 'export const x = 1;' > packages/pkg-a/src/index.ts

open packages/pkg-a/src/index.ts
wait 50

command npm.test
wait 200

# The pty label is "npm test" and CWD is the workspace root, not pkg-a.
# We can verify by checking the pane title does NOT contain "pkg-a".
# (The pty opens: "npm test" in /workspace-root/, not in packages/pkg-a/)
expect screen lacks "no package.json"
# Pane opens successfully — but it's at the wrong cwd (workspace root).
# No way to assert cwd directly in headless; the bug is in the pty profile.
